glew
------------------------------------------
The OpenGL Extension Wrangler Library (GLEW) is a cross-platform 
open-source C/C++ extension loading library. GLEW provides efficient 
run-time mechanisms for determining which OpenGL extensions are 
supported on the target platform. OpenGL core and extension 
functionality is exposed in a single header file.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libGL1-7.2-2
  libGLU1-7.2-2
  libX11_6-1.1.5-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.3-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://glew.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/glew/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack glew-1.5.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./glew-1.5.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glew-1.5.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/glew-1.5.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libGLEW-devel-1.5.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libGLEW1.5-1.5.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(glew)
  /usr/bin/glewinfo.exe
  /usr/bin/visualinfo.exe
  /usr/share/doc/glew-1.5.1/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/glew-1.5.1/README.txt

(libGLEW1.5)
  /usr/bin/cygGLEW-1.5.dll

(libGLEW-devel)
  /usr/include/GL/glew.h
  /usr/include/GL/glxew.h
  /usr/lib/libGLEW.dll.a

------------------

Port Notes:

